      "content": "i get the \"mixed results\" thing, but it feels like you're focusing way more on the chaos that followed than the actual intent. if we look at it through a realist lens, some would say the \"messy aftermath\" is just the price of doing business in foreign policy and doesn't change the fact that the US successfully removed a hostile dictator without a massive troop buildup. shouldn't we view the intervention as a win because it achieved the primary strategic goal of regime change without a long-term occupation?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
